-- Tennis Player Tomic’s Father Is Charged as Partner Hurt
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-05-06T15:55:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-06/tennis-player-tomic-s-father-charged-as-training-partner-hurt.html
The father of  Australia’s top-ranked
tennis player ,  Bernard Tomic , was charged with injuring his
son’s training partner with a head butt.  Ivica Tomic, who is better known as John, denied the
charge, according to a statement released by a spokesman for
 Madrid ’s criminal courts. A hearing scheduled for today was
postponed to May 14. Both the younger and elder Tomic declined
to comment further on the case, the player’s agent, Brian
Cooney, said in an e-mail today.  The training partner, Thomas Drouet of France, sustained a
broken nose in a street in downtown Madrid two days ago, Spanish
police said. The elder Tomic was arrested at a nearby hotel, the
police said.  Tennis Australia , the national governing body for the
sport, said in a statement that the men’s tour is investigating
what happened.  The elder Tomic, who is of Croatian descent, is a former
 taxi driver  who is now coach of his 20-year-old son, according
to the men’s tour website  Bernard Tomic is a member of Australia’s Davis Cup team and
ranked No. 53 on the ATP World Tour. He lost 6-3, 6-2 to  Radek Stepanek  in the first round of the Madrid Masters clay-court
tournament yesterday.  To contact the reporters on this story:
